article.description: Anna Prins and Kelsey Bolte each scored 15 points, leading Iowa State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to a 63-56 victory over Oklahoma (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) on Wednesday night for its second straight victory over a ranked opponent.
article.headline: Prins, Bolte score 15 each for streaking Cyclones
article.linkText: Iowa State balanced in victory over Oklahoma
article.story:
AMES, Iowa -- Anna Prins and Kelsey Bolte each scored 15 points, leading Iowa State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No.22 AP) to a 63-56 victory over Oklahoma (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) on Wednesday night for its second straight victory over a ranked opponent.

Alison Lacey added 12 for the Cyclones (16-3, 4-2 Big 12), who have won four consecutive games after an 0-2 start to the conference season.

Oklahoma (14-5, 4-2) cut a 12-point halftime deficit to 38-35 with 10 1/2 minutes to play and looked to be making a final push.

But Prins, who was 1 of 12 from the field in ISU's win over No. 19 Texas last Saturday, scored six straight points and put the Cyclones back in control. Bolte then had a scoring run of her own, including a 3-pointer from the corner that pushed the lead to 55-46 with 2:57 to play.

Nyeshia Stevenson led Oklahoma in scoring with 14 points. Amanda Thompson added 12 points and 10 rebounds.
